 pair suffered a sharp two-day decline from the 0.7010\u20130.7015 area, dropping to a multi-week low in the vicinity of 0.6865\u20130.6875, a prior reaction zone that attracted buyers on at least three separate occasions. From that base, the recovery has been methodical rather than impulsive \u2014 a series of higher daily lows building through early July, culminating in a strong bullish session on 14 July that broke back above 0.6950 and then a follow-through candle on 15 July that reclaimed the 0.7000 handle. Today's daily candle, however, is notably compressed, printing a high of 0.7011 and a low of 0.6987 at the time of writing \u2014 a clear sign that momentum has stalled as price re-enters the area from which the late-June sell-off originated. The prior reaction zone around 0.6959 now sits as the first meaningful structural support beneath current price, with the 0.6948 level providing a secondary layer. Above, the desk sees no clearly defined resistance until the 0.7184 prior reaction zone, which is a considerable distance from current levels.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the intraday narrative reinforces the neutral bias. Price spiked to 0.7021 during the early Asian session, found no follow-through, and has since oscillated in a tight 30\u201340 pip band between 0.6987 and 0.7011. The hourly candles from mid-morning onwards are small-bodied and overlapping \u2014 a classic consolidation signature. There is no clear directional conviction at the H1 level; buyers have defended the 0.6987\u20130.6995 area on dips, but sellers have capped each attempt toward 0.7010. The market appears to be in a wait-and-see posture.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes the prospect of a scheduled volatility catalyst. In the absence of data, price action is likely to remain range-bound, with liquidity thinner than usual during the North American afternoon. Any unexpected headline risk \u2014 particularly around US-China trade commentary or commodity sentiment \u2014 could 